e                =\n| endtheme                 =\n| composer                 =\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 22\n| list_episodes            = List of Love Island (American TV series) episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Mandy Morris\n* Simon Thomas\n* Ben Thursby-Palmer\n* David George\n* Adam Sher\n* David Eilenberg\n* Richard Foster\n* Chet Fenster\n}}\n| producer                 =\n| location                 = [[Fiji]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-07-01/when-is-love-island-usa-on-tv-who-is-the-host-who-are-the-islanders-where-is-it-filmed-will-we-be-able-to-watch-it-in-the-uk/|title=When is Love Island USA on TV? Who is the host? Who are the Islanders? Where is it filmed? Will we be able to watch it in the UK?|last=Bond|first=Kimberly|date=July 1, 2019|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=Radio Times}}</ref>\n| cinematography           = Quinn Jessop\n| editor                   =\n| camera                   =\n| runtime                  =\n| company                  = ITV Entertainment\n| distributor              = ITV Studios Global Entertainment<br />Motion Content Group\n| budget                   = $30 million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-07-10/love-island-uk-usa-major-differences/|title=What are the major differences between the UK and US versions of Love Island?|last=Bond|first=Kimberly|date=July 10, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019|work=[[RadioTimes]]}}</ref>\n| network                  = [[CBS]]\n| picture_format           =\n| audio_format             =\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|7|9}}\n| last_aired               = {{end date|present}}\n| related                  = ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]''\n| website                  = https://www.cbs.com/shows/love-island/\n| production_website       =\n}}\n'''''Love Island''''' (stylized as '''''love island''''' and also known as '''''Love Island USA''''' outside of the U.S.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.itvstudios.com/catalogue/5420|title=Love Island USA|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=[[ITV Studios]]}}</ref>) is an American [[dating game show|dating]] [[reality show|reality]] show based on the British series ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]''. The series was announced and commissioned on August 8, 2018, by [[CBS]]. It premiered on July 9, 2019, on [[CBS]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Arielle Vandenberg To Host CBS\u2019 \u2018Love Island\u2019 As Reality Dating Series Sets Fiji Location|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/arielle-vandenberg-love-island-1202635510/|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 20, 2019}}</ref> The series is simulcast in Canada on [[CTV Television Network|CTV]].\n\nOn August 1, 2019, the show was renewed for a second season and was originally scheduled to premiere on May 21, 2020. However due to the ongoing [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]] the second season has been placed on hold.\n\n== Format ==\n''Love Island'' involves a group of contestants, referred to as Islanders, living in isolation from the outside world in a villa in [[Fiji]], constantly under video surveillance. To survive in the villa the Islanders must be coupled up with another Islander, whether it be for love, friendship or money, as the overall winning couple receives $100,000. On the first day, the Islanders couple up for the first time based on first impressions, but over the duration of the series, they are forced to \"re-couple\" where they can choose (or be chosen) to remain in their current couple or swap and change.\n\nAny Islander who remains single after the coupling is eliminated and \"dumped\" from the island. Islanders can also be eliminated via a public vote during the series. The public can vote for their favorite couple or who they think is the most compatible through the ''Love Island'' app available on [[smartphones]]. Couples who receive the fewest votes risk being eliminated. Occasionally, twists may occur where the islanders must eliminate each other. During the final week, the public vote for which couple they want to win the series and take home the prize.\n\nWhilst in the villa, each Islander has their own phone with which they can only contact other Islanders via text \u2013 or receive texts informing them of the latest challenges, dumping, or re-coupling. Islanders and couples must typically take part in many games and challenges designed to test their physical and mental abilities, with the winners receiving special prizes afterward. Some Islanders are also sent on dates outside the villa or can win dates by winning challenges.\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn February 22, 2006, it was announced that an American version of ''[[Love Island (2005 TV series)|Celebrity Love Island]]'' was in development at [[MyNetworkTV]], but the show was not produced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadcastingcable.com/news/news-corp-unveils-my-network-tv-78935|title=News Corp. Unveils My Network TV|last1=M. Higgins|first=John|last2=Eggerton|first2=John|date=February 22, 2006|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=[[Broadcasting and Cable]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/02/22/fox-to-launch-my-network-tv-20643/20060222mynetworktv01/|title=FOX to Launch My Network TV|date=February 22, 2006|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref> On August 8, 2018, it was reported that [[CBS]] acquired the rights to an American non-celebrity version of the series from [[ITV Studios]] and Motion Content Group with David George, Adam Sher, and David Eilenberg serving as [[executive producer]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2018/08/08/cbs-secures-us-format-rights-to-international-smash-hit-love-island-for-new-series-order-produced-by-itv-entertainment-791202/20180808cbs01/|title=CBS Secures U.S. Format Rights to International Smash Hit \"Love Island\" for New Series Order Produced by ITV Entertainment|date=August 8, 2018|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=The Futon Critic}}</ref> Simon Thomas, Mandy Morris, Ben Thursby, Richard Foster, and Chet Fenster later joined the series as additional executive producers in addition to the original three.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/05/22/us-viewers-will-get-their-own-love-island-this-summer-981200/20190522cbs02/|title=U.S. Viewers Will Get Their Own \"Love Island\" This Summer|date=May 22, 2019|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=The Futon Critic}}</ref> [[Arielle Vandenberg]] was later announced to be hosting the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/20/actress-and-comedian-arielle-vandenberg-to-host-love-island-this-summer-on-cbs-384304/20190620cbs02/|title=Actress and Comedian Arielle Vandenberg to Host \"Love Island\" This Summer on CBS!|date=June 20, 2019|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=The Futon Critic}}</ref>\n\nThe first season of ''Love Island'' ran from July 9, 2019, to August 7, 2019. The show was renewed for a second season on August 1, 2019, while the first season was still being broadcast. CBS initially announced on February 14, 2020 the second season would premiere on May 21, 2020.<ref name=\"S2 premiere\">{{cite web |last1=Birk |first1=Libby |title='Love Island' Season 2 Premiere Date Announced |url=https://popculture.com/reality-tv/2020/02/14/love-island-season-2-premiere-date-announced/ |website=popculture.com |publisher=popculture. |accessdate=February 14, 2020 |language=English |date=February 14, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The second season was subsequently placed on hold with a new season premiere date to be determined after the network announced on April 7th they would launch ''[[CBS Sunday Movie|Sunday Night at the Movies]]'' for a five week run starting on May 3 due to the ongoing [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"COVID-19-PostponedS2\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/cbs-brings-back-sunday-movie-night-coronavirus-pandemic-paramount-titanic-indiana-jones-mission-impossible-forrest-gump-1202902688/ |title=CBS Brings Back Sunday Movie Night Amid Pandemic With Top Paramount Titles \u2018Titanic\u2019, \u2018Indiana Jones\u2019 & \u2018MI\u2019 |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |last2=Andreeva |first2=Nellie |date=April 7, 2020 |website=Deadline |language=en |access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Broadcast ===\n''Love Island'' opened with a 90-minute premiere on July 9, 2019, and aired every weeknight through August 7, 2019, for a total of twenty-two episodes in its first season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a28321395/how-to-watch-love-island-online-for-free-start-time/|title=How to Watch Love Island Online for Free|last=Dibdin|first=Emma|date=July 8, 2019|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=[[Oprah Magazine]]}}</ref><ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/love-island/listings/|title=Shows A-Z - love island on cbs}}</ref> In addition to the CBS broadcasts, the series is simulcast on [[CTV Television Network|CTV]] in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctv.ca/Love-Island|title=Love Island|accessdate=July 9, 2019|work=[[CTV Television Network|CTV]]}}</ref> \n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Series overview\n| auxA        = Days\n| auxB        = Islanders\n| auxC        = Winner\n| auxD        = Runner-up\n| auxE        = Prize Money\n| infoA  = Average viewers<br />(millions)\n\n| color1      = #FCB1DD\n| link1       = Love Island (American season 1)\n| auxA1       = 31\n| auxB1       = 25\n| auxC1       = Zac Mirabelli<br />Elizabeth Weber\n| auxD1       = Dylan Curry<br />Alexandra Stewart\n| auxE1       = $100,000\n| episodes1   = 22\n| start1      = {{Start date|2019|07|09}}\n| end1        = {{End date|2019|08|07}}\n| infoA1      = 2.19\n\n| color2      = #D7B785\n| link2       = <!--Love Island (American season 2)-->\n| linkR2      = <ref 